WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:44.844 --> 00:00:48.280
Hurry. Get ready to operate.

3
00:00:52.118 --> 00:00:54.109
Hurry up!

4
00:01:02.462 --> 00:01:03.690
It's stillborn.

5
00:01:05.198 --> 00:01:07.598
- Stop the bleeding.
- Wait. one more.

6
00:01:09.936 --> 00:01:11.233
Sponge.

7
00:01:11.438 --> 00:01:13.668
We're losing the mother.
Commence CPR quickly.

8
00:01:13.907 --> 00:01:15.670
Help stop the bleeding.

9
00:01:16.342 --> 00:01:18.503
Hurry. Come help. hurry.

10
00:02:47.934 --> 00:02:49.265
What are you doing here?

11
00:02:49.636 --> 00:02:51.627
Sleeping at your office again tonight?

12
00:02:56.943 --> 00:03:01.209
What's wrong with you?
Is your office really that comfortable?

13
00:03:01.381 --> 00:03:03.474
It stinks worse than the restroom here.

14
00:03:03.716 --> 00:03:07.174
Every day. you don't go home.
you ignore your wife and child.

15
00:03:07.387 --> 00:03:11.289
Just hole yourself up in your
damn office. playing your damn chess.

16
00:03:12.058 --> 00:03:13.923
Who would feel sorry for you?

17
00:03:14.627 --> 00:03:18.961
Do you look like someone working for
the Foreign Affairs unit?

18
00:03:57.537 --> 00:04:00.597
Tai Feng Chemical Group

19
00:05:39.639 --> 00:05:41.539
My brother works for the government.

20
00:05:41.708 --> 00:05:43.608
How long have you worked here?

21
00:05:43.776 --> 00:05:46.802
Miss? Why isn't the air conditioning on?

22
00:05:47.013 --> 00:05:50.244
- Boss told us to turn it off.
- Don't you know how hot it is?

23
00:05:50.450 --> 00:05:55.114
Two hours ago. the boss kept telling me
the office was too cold.

24
00:05:55.288 --> 00:05:59.691
I gave him a blanket.
but still he said it was too cold.

25
00:05:59.892 --> 00:06:02.861
So he told us to turn off
the air conditioning.

26
00:06:03.029 --> 00:06:06.863
You can turn it on now. since your boss
has kicked the bucket.

27
00:06:23.015 --> 00:06:24.949
What is the situation?

28
00:06:26.018 --> 00:06:29.249
Captain. do you know who he is?

29
00:06:29.422 --> 00:06:31.253
The chairman
of the Tai Feng Corporation.

30
00:06:33.526 --> 00:06:35.926
The one who dumped toxic waste...

31
00:06:36.162 --> 00:06:37.390
...into the river?
- Yes.

32
00:06:37.997 --> 00:06:38.986
Come with me.

33
00:06:39.165 --> 00:06:43.693
The medics took one look at him
and called us.

34
00:06:46.539 --> 00:06:50.805
It's ridiculous.
I believe he was drowned...

35
00:06:50.977 --> 00:06:53.207
...in icy water.

36
00:06:53.446 --> 00:06:55.812
The mucus in his
nasal cavities is frozen.

37
00:06:56.115 --> 00:06:57.480
Drowned?

38
00:07:11.431 --> 00:07:14.832
You are with Foreign Affairs.
This is not your case.

39
00:07:15.034 --> 00:07:16.661
What are you doing here?

40
00:07:17.336 --> 00:07:19.031
Might this not be
the original crime scene?

41
00:07:19.205 --> 00:07:24.666
This scene is perfectly intact. And his
employees say he never left his office.

42
00:07:25.178 --> 00:07:28.011
- What case?
- I said. I have a case here.

43
00:07:28.781 --> 00:07:32.842
On such a hot day as today.
the boss of a major corporation...

44
00:07:33.019 --> 00:07:37.046
...drowns in his 17th-floor office.

45
00:07:41.828 --> 00:07:44.558
What the hell are you doing here?

46
00:07:45.665 --> 00:07:47.724
What case are you on?

47
00:07:49.035 --> 00:07:51.503
- What are you doing?
- What is he doing here?

48
00:07:51.704 --> 00:07:52.728
Captain.

49
00:07:54.073 --> 00:07:56.633
Huo-tu. you have no business here.
Go back.

50
00:08:07.453 --> 00:08:09.353
- Espin Pinosa?
- Yes. sir.

51
00:08:09.522 --> 00:08:10.648
I've got to bring you in...

52
00:08:10.857 --> 00:08:14.588
...for violating Taiwan's
labor agreement with the Philippines.

53
00:08:14.794 --> 00:08:16.762
- Understand?
- I don't understand.

54
00:08:17.663 --> 00:08:20.131
I'm arresting you.

55
00:08:20.366 --> 00:08:22.527
No! Why? Why's that?

56
00:08:22.702 --> 00:08:24.135
Why is that? No.

57
00:08:25.872 --> 00:08:26.861
No...

58
00:08:51.898 --> 00:08:53.763
Mei-mei. go outside.

59
00:08:54.367 --> 00:08:56.130
Mommy wants to talk to Daddy.

60
00:08:57.803 --> 00:08:58.792
Mei-mei.

61
00:09:01.340 --> 00:09:02.398
Mei-mei.

62
00:09:09.015 --> 00:09:13.281
- What happened to her neck?
- That was last week's news.

63
00:09:13.853 --> 00:09:17.482
Her classmate shot at her
with a toy gun at naptime.

64
00:09:18.658 --> 00:09:22.253
Didn't I tell you
not to bring Mei-mei here?

65
00:09:27.033 --> 00:09:29.126
When was the last time you came home?

66
00:09:31.137 --> 00:09:32.832
The teacher wants a meeting
with her parents.

67
00:09:33.306 --> 00:09:37.037
I cannot take another day off.
You go this time.

68
00:09:46.118 --> 00:09:48.518
I'll take these clothes home to wash.

69
00:09:55.394 --> 00:09:58.795
I think Mei-mei should stay with you.

70
00:09:58.998 --> 00:10:01.489
It's better for her
to be with her mother.

71
00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:05.268
Why make us miserable too?

72
00:10:07.506 --> 00:10:09.497
Mei-mei. we're going home.

73
00:10:29.528 --> 00:10:31.462
I've never seen anything like it.

74
00:10:32.098 --> 00:10:35.659
His epidermal and dermal layers
were completely frozen.

75
00:10:37.670 --> 00:10:41.128
How is that possible?
Is there water in his lungs?

76
00:10:41.607 --> 00:10:43.268
Not one drop.

77
00:10:43.609 --> 00:10:45.270
But his brain...

78
00:10:46.145 --> 00:10:48.010
Come look at this.

79
00:10:49.181 --> 00:10:53.811
This is the thalamus. Seat of
the nervous system. Guess what that is?

80
00:10:54.754 --> 00:10:55.812
What is it?

81
00:10:57.456 --> 00:11:01.984
- It looks like mold.
- Yes. It is mold bacteria.

82
00:11:03.362 --> 00:11:08.493
This was scraped out of his sinus
cavity. same bacteria as in his brain.

83
00:11:09.835 --> 00:11:11.996
What did you put for cause of death?

84
00:11:16.575 --> 00:11:18.566
"Suspected drowning."

85
00:11:20.146 --> 00:11:22.478
- Is that a good thing to do?
- No.

86
00:11:22.748 --> 00:11:23.737
It's not good at all.

87
00:11:25.818 --> 00:11:28.446
- Is it toxic?
- Don't know.

88
00:11:28.988 --> 00:11:32.719
Taiwan can't find out.
Our technology is too far behind.

89
00:11:35.995 --> 00:11:37.792
Where can we find out?

90
00:11:39.632 --> 00:11:42.760
Quantico. Virginia. U.S.A.

91
00:11:43.235 --> 00:11:46.204
FBI ACADEMY

92
00:11:52.478 --> 00:11:53.775
Anyway...

93
00:11:54.447 --> 00:11:56.176
...the U.S. Is not
only the biggest producer...

94
00:11:56.415 --> 00:11:58.906
...of movies
and nuclear weapons.

95
00:11:59.185 --> 00:12:01.483
We're also number one
in serial killers.

96
00:12:02.655 --> 00:12:04.748
Now. when we give these classes...

97
00:12:05.357 --> 00:12:07.917
...what the bureau doesn't want us
to tell you is that...

98
00:12:09.195 --> 00:12:10.753
...we still fail.

99
00:12:12.031 --> 00:12:14.158
Every rule has its exception...

100
00:12:14.500 --> 00:12:17.867
...and you learn from failure.
So...

101
00:12:19.472 --> 00:12:20.871
...let's start there.

102
00:12:24.176 --> 00:12:27.509
Okay. in 1994.
a total of nine corpses...

103
00:12:27.713 --> 00:12:30.648
...were found
in the suburbs of St. Louis.

104
00:12:30.950 --> 00:12:32.815
All boys...

105
00:12:33.018 --> 00:12:37.148
...all found lying like this:

106
00:12:37.656 --> 00:12:42.559
Posed. facedown.
Cause of death was strangulation.

107
00:12:43.028 --> 00:12:46.862
There were no bruises.
no signs of struggle.

108
00:12:47.133 --> 00:12:49.101
No evidence of molestation either.

109
00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:51.365
All the victims were runaways.

110
00:12:51.971 --> 00:12:54.804
Kids who slipped through the cracks.
et cetera.

111
00:12:56.108 --> 00:12:58.303
I drew up a profile
of the type we call the...

112
00:12:58.477 --> 00:13:02.072
..."preferential offender."
Street predator.

113
00:13:02.548 --> 00:13:05.073
White male. of course.

114
00:13:05.918 --> 00:13:09.410
Loner. Out of work or itinerant.

115
00:13:09.789 --> 00:13:13.281
Socially inept.
sexually repressed. an outcast.

116
00:13:13.492 --> 00:13:15.255
But when the killer
turned himself in...

117
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:18.294
- He surrendered?
- Yes.

118
00:13:18.564 --> 00:13:21.624
Walked into his local police department.

119
00:13:22.768 --> 00:13:25.066
As if that wasn't embarrassing enough...

120
00:13:25.337 --> 00:13:28.738
...we soon found that except
for the "white male" part...

121
00:13:28.908 --> 00:13:33.777
...he did not correspond
to one single detail of my profile.

122
00:13:35.447 --> 00:13:38.416
In fact. I couldn't have been
any more wrong.

123
00:13:43.989 --> 00:13:45.923
That's not even the strange part.

124
00:13:46.158 --> 00:13:49.218
The strange part were the victims'
expressions.

125
00:13:57.269 --> 00:13:59.294
Are they smiling?

126
00:14:00.406 --> 00:14:03.000
Sure appears that way. doesn't it?

127
00:14:05.978 --> 00:14:09.345
Almost as if they were on
some kind of a high...

128
00:14:09.515 --> 00:14:11.073
...at the moment of their deaths...

129
00:14:12.351 --> 00:14:14.251
...in a state of bliss.

130
00:14:19.191 --> 00:14:23.787
HSIN-YI DISTRICT. TAIPEl

131
00:15:16.782 --> 00:15:20.309
Fire department?
My home is on fire.

132
00:15:22.187 --> 00:15:25.156
I'm at Alley 200. Section 3.
Hsin-yi Road...

133
00:15:35.634 --> 00:15:40.571
SENATOR'S WIFE
TO SUE CHIU FOR ADULTERY

134
00:15:50.316 --> 00:15:52.546
I've never experienced
this kind of situation before.

135
00:15:52.785 --> 00:15:57.188
- Of course I'm scared.
- I am too.

136
00:15:57.823 --> 00:15:59.085
She's the one?

137
00:15:59.591 --> 00:16:02.651
- The senator's mistress?
- She's the one.

138
00:16:02.828 --> 00:16:04.557
Bailed out just this morning.

139
00:16:05.764 --> 00:16:07.254
Who reported this?

140
00:16:08.400 --> 00:16:12.234
She called the fire department
an hour ago to report a fire.

141
00:16:12.471 --> 00:16:15.497
- They hurried over.
- And no sign of a fire at all.

142
00:16:15.808 --> 00:16:16.968
No.

143
00:16:19.011 --> 00:16:22.276
Your face looks worse than hers.

144
00:16:25.617 --> 00:16:26.982
Look at her arms.

145
00:16:28.153 --> 00:16:31.020
This peculiar kind of contortion...

146
00:16:31.290 --> 00:16:33.656
...is caused by severe
muscular dehydration.

147
00:16:33.826 --> 00:16:36.192
This situation only happens to...

148
00:16:36.462 --> 00:16:40.523
...corpses burned to death
at very high temperatures.

149
00:16:41.100 --> 00:16:42.761
But here...

150
00:16:43.302 --> 00:16:44.701
How could it be?

151
00:16:48.941 --> 00:16:50.203
"Suspected murder...

152
00:16:50.676 --> 00:16:52.143
...cause of death unknown"?

153
00:16:52.911 --> 00:16:53.900
This doesn't look good.

154
00:16:54.146 --> 00:16:56.671
My report is based on current evidence.

155
00:16:56.915 --> 00:17:00.248
And I feel both cases are related.

156
00:17:01.620 --> 00:17:05.283
Re-examine the corpse.
Rewrite the report.

157
00:17:06.825 --> 00:17:08.452
As if we don't have
enough problems already.

158
00:17:08.660 --> 00:17:12.118
Getting tangled up in
a politician's personal affairs.

159
00:17:14.199 --> 00:17:16.030
Re-examine her heart.

160
00:17:16.268 --> 00:17:21.433
People die of heart attacks every day!

161
00:17:22.708 --> 00:17:25.768
TEACHERS' OFFICE

162
00:17:26.211 --> 00:17:29.078
This is Su Chao-pin.
He cut your daughter's hair...

163
00:17:29.381 --> 00:17:32.111
...during naptime today.

164
00:17:32.451 --> 00:17:36.012
Then she scratched his eye.

165
00:17:36.188 --> 00:17:38.019
Last week...

166
00:17:38.223 --> 00:17:41.989
This is Huang Chin-feng.
Your daughter fought with him.

167
00:17:42.327 --> 00:17:45.057
Mr. Huang. excuse me...

168
00:17:45.297 --> 00:17:47.356
...I risk offense to ask a question.

169
00:17:47.533 --> 00:17:50.969
I am thinking. would it be better
if you sent her...

170
00:17:51.537 --> 00:17:53.300
...to a special school?

171
00:18:16.462 --> 00:18:18.225
Huang Mei-mei's parent.

172
00:18:19.431 --> 00:18:21.262
Huang Mei-mei's parent.

173
00:18:44.256 --> 00:18:46.315
Has she been taking her medication?

174
00:18:47.126 --> 00:18:50.960
I don't know. I suppose so.

175
00:18:51.263 --> 00:18:52.491
You "suppose"?

176
00:19:27.599 --> 00:19:31.899
She hates taking them.
But I haven't been home recently.

177
00:19:32.137 --> 00:19:35.698
The pills don't work so well.
But she should take them.

178
00:20:54.886 --> 00:20:58.947
CHURCH OF NEW TRUTH. TAMSUI

179
00:21:59.217 --> 00:22:00.411
Hello?

180
00:22:02.054 --> 00:22:03.078
What?

181
00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:29.508
Mei-mei. it's just a dream.

182
00:22:36.488 --> 00:22:38.479
JIAN MING LEGAL SERVICES

183
00:22:42.494 --> 00:22:44.758
DIVORCE AGREEMENT

184
00:23:12.557 --> 00:23:16.220
Father Lorenzo died
in his own room last night.

185
00:23:16.628 --> 00:23:17.788
Murdered.

186
00:23:18.296 --> 00:23:21.424
This case is sensitive
because of his identity.

187
00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:24.228
Taiwan must go through this man
to buy weapons from America.

188
00:23:24.469 --> 00:23:27.267
The foreign press will be here.
you deal with them.

189
00:23:27.472 --> 00:23:30.999
I have left Homicide.
Leave me alone. would you?

190
00:23:31.176 --> 00:23:33.736
Foreign Affairs handles
foreigners in Taiwan.

191
00:23:33.979 --> 00:23:36.573
And you speak the best English.
It's all yours.

192
00:23:41.953 --> 00:23:43.079
What happened?

193
00:23:43.989 --> 00:23:46.856
Time of death. 3 a.m.

194
00:23:47.025 --> 00:23:50.256
There were at least two murderers.

195
00:23:50.929 --> 00:23:55.263
While the victim was asleep.
they disemboweled him.

196
00:24:00.672 --> 00:24:04.130
This is intestinal fat
that insulates our intestines.

197
00:24:04.309 --> 00:24:07.801
After the suspects
cut open Lorenzo's belly...

198
00:24:07.979 --> 00:24:11.676
...they took out his intestines.
washed them with water...

199
00:24:11.850 --> 00:24:15.115
...replaced them and sewed him up.

200
00:24:17.789 --> 00:24:21.657
He lasted at least two hours
before he died.

201
00:24:22.294 --> 00:24:24.694
It looks as though
he had been held down...

202
00:24:24.963 --> 00:24:28.524
...but his wrists
have sustained no injuries.

203
00:24:36.341 --> 00:24:39.242
Now will you still say those people...

204
00:24:40.045 --> 00:24:42.673
...died naturally of heart attacks?

205
00:24:45.717 --> 00:24:49.551
After an initial investigation.
we have discovered that...

206
00:24:49.721 --> 00:24:54.624
...the deaths of Father Lorenzo.
the chairman of Tai Feng...

207
00:24:54.793 --> 00:24:59.958
...and Chiu Miao-fang are
all possibly related.

208
00:25:00.298 --> 00:25:03.597
These are serial murders.

209
00:25:03.768 --> 00:25:05.235
Because this case...

210
00:25:07.973 --> 00:25:10.032
Let the chief finish.

211
00:25:10.242 --> 00:25:14.736
Because this case
has generated many rumors...

212
00:25:14.980 --> 00:25:18.211
...causing anxiety among our society...

213
00:25:18.383 --> 00:25:22.319
...our police force wishes
to solve this crime logically.

214
00:25:22.487 --> 00:25:26.048
Through the American Institute
in Taiwan...

215
00:25:26.224 --> 00:25:31.389
...the FBI has agreed to send an agent
specializing in serial murder...

216
00:25:31.596 --> 00:25:34.064
...to Taiwan to assist
in solving this case.

217
00:25:34.399 --> 00:25:39.666
We hope he can use a scientific method
to move us forward.

218
00:25:40.772 --> 00:25:42.262
Chief...

219
00:25:42.574 --> 00:25:44.633
A question from Miss Chow. please.

220
00:25:45.310 --> 00:25:48.211
Are you giving in
to political pressure?

221
00:25:48.413 --> 00:25:52.110
Also. what about Taiwan's
judicial independence?

222
00:25:52.551 --> 00:25:55.816
Everyone. I am announcing that...

223
00:25:56.154 --> 00:26:00.921
...this FBI investigator doesn't
have the right to bear arms. arrest...

224
00:26:01.159 --> 00:26:03.218
...nor interrogate.

225
00:26:03.562 --> 00:26:06.360
The legal investigation rights
are clear.

226
00:26:06.765 --> 00:26:10.929
Rumors say there are talismans on
the corpse. Was it a cult ritual?

227
00:26:11.102 --> 00:26:13.161
No such thing.

228
00:26:13.371 --> 00:26:15.362
What's the name of the agent?

229
00:26:17.976 --> 00:26:20.501
His name is Kevin Richter.

230
00:26:21.947 --> 00:26:23.346
- How do you spell that?
- How do you spell that?

231
00:26:23.548 --> 00:26:24.981
- How do you spell that?
- How do you spell that?

232
00:26:25.216 --> 00:26:29.550
R-l-C-H-T-E-R.

233
00:26:54.980 --> 00:26:56.004
Bye.

234
00:27:31.516 --> 00:27:32.505
What a nut!

235
00:27:34.119 --> 00:27:35.677
That was my husband.

236
00:27:41.993 --> 00:27:43.460
What is the murderer like?

237
00:27:43.628 --> 00:27:46.654
Are there any political agendas
for your trip?

238
00:27:46.965 --> 00:27:48.159
Do you speak Chinese?

239
00:27:48.333 --> 00:27:51.860
How will you investigate
without speaking Chinese?

240
00:27:54.439 --> 00:27:57.431
Do you know an officer
named Huang Huo-tu?

241
00:28:39.384 --> 00:28:41.818
You want to listen to some music?

242
00:28:43.154 --> 00:28:45.588
And ruin this conversation?

243
00:28:49.794 --> 00:28:51.659
Yeah. sure. Fine with me.

244
00:29:30.001 --> 00:29:33.164
The same mold was
found in the brains...

245
00:29:33.371 --> 00:29:34.963
...and nasal cavities of the victims.

246
00:29:35.140 --> 00:29:39.008
Whether it's toxic and how it entered
the bodies of the victims...

247
00:29:39.177 --> 00:29:41.771
...will depend on the report
from America.

248
00:29:43.281 --> 00:29:45.681
There are no obvious motives
to the murders.

249
00:29:45.850 --> 00:29:48.375
And they did not know one another.

250
00:29:48.686 --> 00:29:50.984
On the body of the third victim...

251
00:29:51.156 --> 00:29:54.284
...a Taoist talisman painted
with the victim's blood.

252
00:29:54.459 --> 00:29:56.950
We have checked
with the Taoist Society.

253
00:29:57.162 --> 00:29:58.823
They've never seen it before.

254
00:29:59.164 --> 00:30:00.358
It should be related to Taoism.

255
00:30:00.732 --> 00:30:04.429
Yes. I wanted to... Excuse me.
Hold on...

256
00:30:06.704 --> 00:30:07.693
I'm sorry.

257
00:30:07.872 --> 00:30:10.306
Tell them they shouldn't count on...

258
00:30:10.542 --> 00:30:11.770
...a Taoist organization for help.

259
00:30:11.943 --> 00:30:14.036
He said we shouldn't
have done that.

260
00:30:14.279 --> 00:30:18.045
What we want is an expert.
a scholar...

261
00:30:18.249 --> 00:30:22.151
...in religious studies
from a university maybe. or...

262
00:30:24.022 --> 00:30:26.183
He said we should ask a scholar.

263
00:30:29.994 --> 00:30:31.359
That's it.

264
00:30:32.330 --> 00:30:33.763
Did you explain how. how...?

265
00:30:36.734 --> 00:30:40.170
Okay. All right. look. this is...

266
00:30:41.339 --> 00:30:44.740
Do we know why the killer
picked these victims?

267
00:30:44.909 --> 00:30:48.310
Anyone know why the victims
were chosen?

268
00:30:49.047 --> 00:30:52.574
It seems to me that's the top priority
of our investigation.

269
00:30:52.884 --> 00:30:54.374
Everything else is a waste of time.

270
00:30:54.552 --> 00:30:56.076
Everything else is a waste of time.

271
00:30:56.254 --> 00:30:59.018
Didn't we just say
there's no obvious motive?

272
00:30:59.257 --> 00:31:01.748
Is this material from a textbook?

273
00:31:02.126 --> 00:31:04.560
Why come all the way
to tell us this?

274
00:31:04.729 --> 00:31:07.197
Who is in charge?
Who is in charge?

275
00:31:07.832 --> 00:31:11.063
All right. stop it.

276
00:31:12.704 --> 00:31:14.296
What are they saying?

277
00:31:15.540 --> 00:31:18.475
"Thank you." and they'll
consider your suggestions.

278
00:31:21.512 --> 00:31:23.002
I can see that.

279
00:31:23.314 --> 00:31:24.679
That's all for today.

280
00:31:24.949 --> 00:31:25.973
No questions. right?

281
00:31:26.150 --> 00:31:27.242
That's it for today.

282
00:31:28.019 --> 00:31:32.456
If someone can take me
to Lorenzo's murder scene...

283
00:31:32.657 --> 00:31:34.454
How tall can a person get?

284
00:31:42.033 --> 00:31:44.593
I had these blessed for our safety.

285
00:31:44.802 --> 00:31:46.827
Sit down. Sit down.

286
00:31:50.675 --> 00:31:52.438
- Excuse me.
- What. what?

287
00:31:52.644 --> 00:31:54.509
Sit down. please.

288
00:31:57.682 --> 00:32:00.310
He wants to go
to Lorenzo's murder scene.

289
00:32:00.518 --> 00:32:03.043
Not necessary. We checked
everything out in detail.

290
00:32:03.221 --> 00:32:04.210
And took photographs.

291
00:32:04.422 --> 00:32:05.787
He says it's not necessary.

292
00:32:05.990 --> 00:32:07.218
Bullshit.

293
00:32:10.395 --> 00:32:11.987
That's bullshit.

294
00:32:13.531 --> 00:32:14.998
Go ahead. translate it.

295
00:32:15.199 --> 00:32:17.292
- I don't have to. They know.
- Good.

296
00:32:17.502 --> 00:32:19.026
It's very necessary.

297
00:32:19.237 --> 00:32:21.933
It's what I do.
It's why I'm here.

298
00:32:28.680 --> 00:32:29.942
You take him there.

299
00:32:30.782 --> 00:32:34.240
But I don't know anything about this.

300
00:32:36.087 --> 00:32:38.453
- He said it's okay.
- Good.

301
00:32:39.757 --> 00:32:41.520
Well. then...

302
00:32:42.627 --> 00:32:43.992
Thank your mother.

303
00:32:46.998 --> 00:32:48.625
Thank your mother.

304
00:32:50.468 --> 00:32:51.457
We. we...

305
00:32:51.636 --> 00:32:54.298
It's "Thank you very much." right?

306
00:32:54.539 --> 00:32:55.801
Right.

307
00:32:58.710 --> 00:33:00.701
This is Taoist. isn't it?

308
00:33:02.847 --> 00:33:04.678
Can I offer advice?

309
00:33:04.949 --> 00:33:09.045
You should be more respectful.
Not talk so much.

310
00:33:09.454 --> 00:33:10.785
Thanks.

311
00:33:11.823 --> 00:33:14.656
I'll consider your suggestion.

312
00:33:17.395 --> 00:33:18.828
You are a foreigner.

313
00:33:19.831 --> 00:33:23.426
I'm saying. if you don't
want to cause trouble.

314
00:33:23.601 --> 00:33:25.660
I'm surprised at you. Huo-tu.

315
00:33:26.604 --> 00:33:29.266
I didn't figure you
for the cautious type.

316
00:33:30.274 --> 00:33:32.970
- That's not your reputation.
- What do you mean?

317
00:33:49.560 --> 00:33:51.027
You researched my background?

318
00:33:51.462 --> 00:33:53.657
I like to know my partners.

319
00:33:53.898 --> 00:33:57.026
This story is why
the AIT recommended you.

320
00:33:57.235 --> 00:34:00.295
They don't have much confidence
in your police force.

321
00:34:00.972 --> 00:34:02.701
They got it all wrong.

322
00:34:03.508 --> 00:34:07.069
I'm no different than any other
policeman on the force.

323
00:34:07.245 --> 00:34:10.544
And I regret very much
my naive behavior.

324
00:34:12.417 --> 00:34:15.580
What do you have to say
about your corruption trial?

325
00:34:26.397 --> 00:34:29.628
Huang Huo-tu. you bastard!

326
00:34:29.934 --> 00:34:32.061
How can you sleep at night?

327
00:34:32.270 --> 00:34:35.103
What kind of cousin are you?

328
00:34:35.273 --> 00:34:36.331
Officer Huang!

329
00:34:41.279 --> 00:34:42.473
Watch out!

330
00:34:54.258 --> 00:34:58.820
Listen. I was assigned to this case.
I got no choice.

331
00:34:58.996 --> 00:35:02.329
And you are not going to get
any special treatment from me.

332
00:35:04.168 --> 00:35:05.465
Got it.

333
00:35:06.304 --> 00:35:09.296
Do me a favor and try
not to kill me. okay?

334
00:35:30.595 --> 00:35:33.530
So this is where the dead guy was?

335
00:35:33.698 --> 00:35:34.926
Yes.

336
00:35:39.203 --> 00:35:43.970
- What's this?
- <i>Lung Chi-ji.</i> air conditioner.

337
00:35:49.213 --> 00:35:51.204
Let's just see.

338
00:35:57.922 --> 00:36:02.052
Were there air conditioners
at the other crime scenes?

339
00:36:03.494 --> 00:36:08.124
The whole city has them.
It's hot. Why?

340
00:36:14.105 --> 00:36:16.073
Do you have any idea...

341
00:36:17.842 --> 00:36:19.332
...what this is?

342
00:36:23.214 --> 00:36:25.944
This is the pellet found
in Lorenzo's room.

343
00:36:26.217 --> 00:36:29.948
This is from Chiu Miao-fang's
air conditioner.

344
00:36:30.588 --> 00:36:35.525
This was found on the floor
of Chairman Liao's office.

345
00:36:38.462 --> 00:36:41.590
They were from the same device.

346
00:36:42.366 --> 00:36:46.860
- What device?
- Possibly a converted air rifle.

347
00:36:47.071 --> 00:36:50.268
- These people are amazing.
- Why do you say that?

348
00:36:50.474 --> 00:36:53.466
To hollow out
and drill three holes...

349
00:36:53.644 --> 00:36:56.442
...requires advanced technology.

350
00:36:56.681 --> 00:36:58.148
Besides...

351
00:36:59.350 --> 00:37:00.612
...Iook...

352
00:37:00.818 --> 00:37:04.254
...it's the same bacteria
found in the victims.

353
00:37:04.422 --> 00:37:09.792
So the killers put the mold
into the hollowed-out pellets...

354
00:37:10.261 --> 00:37:13.788
...then shot them into
the air-conditioning vents...

355
00:37:14.031 --> 00:37:16.499
...for the bacteria to dissipate.
- Correct.

356
00:37:29.380 --> 00:37:30.779
How are you?

357
00:37:32.650 --> 00:37:34.641
Hello there. how you doing?

358
00:37:37.922 --> 00:37:39.116
What's the matter?

359
00:37:39.657 --> 00:37:41.056
You shy?

360
00:37:42.393 --> 00:37:44.384
Well. I'm just wondering...

361
00:37:44.729 --> 00:37:48.187
...what you're doing here
all by yourself.

362
00:37:50.301 --> 00:37:53.168
My name is Kevin.

363
00:37:57.541 --> 00:37:58.565
Yours?

364
00:37:59.477 --> 00:38:01.240
- What's your...?
- Her name is Mei-mei.

365
00:38:04.649 --> 00:38:06.310
She's my daughter.

366
00:38:06.751 --> 00:38:09.845
I was just trying
to make her smile.

367
00:38:10.521 --> 00:38:13.684
I apologize.
She's scared of strangers.

368
00:38:13.891 --> 00:38:15.882
Not at all.
You taught her right.

369
00:38:16.994 --> 00:38:19.019
- Kevin Richter.
- I know.

370
00:38:19.397 --> 00:38:24.425
- I'm the wife of Officer Huang Huo-tu.
- Oh. really?

371
00:38:24.802 --> 00:38:27.168
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Me too.

372
00:38:27.405 --> 00:38:28.929
Your husband. He's a...

373
00:38:29.206 --> 00:38:30.639
You know. he's...

374
00:38:31.842 --> 00:38:34.402
He's a very interesting guy.

375
00:38:34.745 --> 00:38:36.679
Yeah. he is.

376
00:38:37.815 --> 00:38:39.578
Thank you for lying.

377
00:38:40.551 --> 00:38:41.540
Anytime.

378
00:38:41.719 --> 00:38:43.949
Remember how I turned up
at Tai Feng...

379
00:38:44.188 --> 00:38:47.180
...to arrest an illegal
foreign worker?

380
00:38:48.459 --> 00:38:49.721
Well?

381
00:38:50.695 --> 00:38:52.629
I found out from the papers...

382
00:38:53.898 --> 00:38:56.264
...I checked the other two victims.

383
00:38:56.534 --> 00:38:59.230
They were in the papers
and were killed thereafter.

384
00:38:59.403 --> 00:39:04.466
TAI FENG DUMPS TO XIC WASTE
ILLEGAL LABORER WON'T TESTIFY

385
00:39:04.642 --> 00:39:08.271
Huo-tu. I have to tell you one thing.

386
00:39:09.914 --> 00:39:13.873
Chief is concerned about that FBI man.
You must be careful.

387
00:39:15.119 --> 00:39:16.814
Have you thought that...

388
00:39:17.154 --> 00:39:19.816
...no matter what this Richter...

389
00:39:19.990 --> 00:39:24.120
...comes up with in the end or not...

390
00:39:24.395 --> 00:39:27.057
...your life will be different?

391
00:39:27.631 --> 00:39:28.893
Think about it.

392
00:39:29.100 --> 00:39:33.264
Let's say. because of him.
the case really does move ahead.

393
00:39:33.504 --> 00:39:36.632
How do you think the men will feel?

394
00:39:40.010 --> 00:39:42.911
You will be even worse off.

395
00:39:45.449 --> 00:39:48.350
He was called in just to do a show.

396
00:39:48.586 --> 00:39:51.419
Just help him finish his show.

397
00:39:53.691 --> 00:39:54.988
Besides...

398
00:39:56.460 --> 00:40:00.453
I don't think the chief believes
this case can be cracked.

399
00:40:00.865 --> 00:40:04.699
Just watch.
He'll be looking for a scapegoat.

400
00:40:05.803 --> 00:40:09.170
- It can't be cracked?
- Are you an idiot?

401
00:40:09.440 --> 00:40:11.431
Use your head.

402
00:40:12.476 --> 00:40:14.842
This is not even a normal case.

403
00:40:16.647 --> 00:40:18.808
How many years since the academy?

404
00:40:19.016 --> 00:40:22.645
Twenty? Have you seen
such a thing in 20 years?

405
00:40:23.954 --> 00:40:26.422
Or heard anything like it?

406
00:40:28.259 --> 00:40:29.556
Let me tell you...

407
00:40:30.294 --> 00:40:35.755
...it may not have been
committed by a human.

408
00:40:39.737 --> 00:40:41.796
Now you've gone too far.

409
00:40:42.273 --> 00:40:46.004
Today I stand in the position
of your friend...

410
00:40:46.277 --> 00:40:49.178
...although being your friend
sure as hell isn't easy...

411
00:40:49.413 --> 00:40:51.176
...I still must tell you...

412
00:40:51.515 --> 00:40:54.746
...you are facing
a hopeless chess game.

413
00:40:54.952 --> 00:40:57.682
The best way is to give up...

414
00:40:57.922 --> 00:40:59.981
...and save your own skin.

415
00:41:08.332 --> 00:41:12.496
You mean she hasn't
spoken in two years?

416
00:41:14.338 --> 00:41:18.502
- Not one word?
- Nothing. Ever since the incident.

417
00:41:19.643 --> 00:41:23.511
You're talking about the abduction?

418
00:41:25.349 --> 00:41:27.840
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

419
00:41:31.388 --> 00:41:32.753
What's going on?

420
00:41:39.697 --> 00:41:42.530
Don't lose it again.
Each copy costs $ 150.

421
00:41:42.800 --> 00:41:47.464
I am busy. When I'm done.
I'll complete the application.

422
00:41:47.872 --> 00:41:51.535
You're too busy to sign your name?

423
00:41:54.478 --> 00:41:56.139
I have to make arrangements.

424
00:41:56.413 --> 00:41:58.608
What have you done
for the past two years?

425
00:42:02.152 --> 00:42:06.589
I spoke with my parents.
You won't have to be responsible.

426
00:42:09.059 --> 00:42:10.219
And our daughter?

427
00:42:10.895 --> 00:42:14.558
I'll bring her to Canada.
They have specialists there.

428
00:42:14.999 --> 00:42:17.229
She needs help.

429
00:42:17.801 --> 00:42:21.532
- She has a whole life ahead of her.
- Very well.

430
00:42:21.739 --> 00:42:23.570
Thanks for taking the trouble.

431
00:42:25.943 --> 00:42:27.570
Let's go. Mei-mei.

432
00:42:29.680 --> 00:42:32.547
- It was nice to meet you.
- Pleasure was all mine.

433
00:42:33.851 --> 00:42:37.617
- And good luck. You will need it.
- Thank you. Bye-bye.

434
00:42:37.855 --> 00:42:38.844
Bye-bye.

435
00:42:46.096 --> 00:42:47.859
ACADEMIA SINICA

436
00:42:48.999 --> 00:42:51.365
DR. SHENG ZU CHANG.
SOCIAL ANTHROPOLOG Y

437
00:43:03.380 --> 00:43:04.540
Amazing.

438
00:43:04.982 --> 00:43:07.678
This talisman is fairly new.

439
00:43:08.619 --> 00:43:10.678
Several years ago...

440
00:43:10.955 --> 00:43:14.857
...a Taoist temple was unearthed
in Jiao Chi. China...

441
00:43:15.059 --> 00:43:17.027
...called the True Sage Temple.

442
00:43:17.661 --> 00:43:22.997
Inside. they discovered writing
carved into the stone.

443
00:43:23.233 --> 00:43:27.465
Some religious implements
and talismanic relics.

444
00:43:28.806 --> 00:43:31.206
These are the photographs.

445
00:44:04.541 --> 00:44:05.803
This way. please.

446
00:44:27.297 --> 00:44:30.391
TRUE SAGE TEMPLE

447
00:44:30.934 --> 00:44:33.266
Do you understand?

448
00:44:34.271 --> 00:44:36.296
The talisman on
the foreigner's body...

449
00:44:36.740 --> 00:44:40.733
...is the same as those
discovered a few years ago.

450
00:44:40.944 --> 00:44:43.640
- What does the talisman represent?
- <i>Gou Di.</i>

451
00:44:44.114 --> 00:44:45.672
<i>Gou Di?</i>

452
00:44:45.949 --> 00:44:48.281
A summons to the underworld.

453
00:44:48.652 --> 00:44:52.850
A death curse
from the king of hell.

454
00:45:32.229 --> 00:45:33.924
FRIGID HELL

455
00:45:38.268 --> 00:45:40.566
TONGUE-REMOVAL HELL

456
00:45:41.972 --> 00:45:43.963
DISEMBOWELMENT HELL

457
00:45:47.811 --> 00:45:49.608
HEART-EXTRACTING HELL

458
00:46:15.072 --> 00:46:18.132
And the stone carvings...

459
00:46:18.375 --> 00:46:23.972
It is all in code.
We don't know what they mean...

460
00:46:24.148 --> 00:46:28.744
...we can't make out the text.
It's a complete puzzle.

461
00:46:31.355 --> 00:46:33.687
This is a copy of the same scriptures
in modern characters.

462
00:46:34.591 --> 00:46:38.789
But they still don't make any sense.

463
00:46:39.163 --> 00:46:41.961
- What about these diagrams?
- They're common.

464
00:46:42.366 --> 00:46:44.698
They're basic Taoist visions.

465
00:46:45.669 --> 00:46:47.899
Taoism believes that
through this system...

466
00:46:48.071 --> 00:46:50.437
...it's possible to see
into the past and future.

467
00:46:50.808 --> 00:46:52.799
It depicts
the universe of Taoism.

468
00:46:53.076 --> 00:46:58.070
Mahjong and Chinese chess...

469
00:46:58.248 --> 00:46:59.977
...through minor examples...

470
00:47:00.450 --> 00:47:03.908
...have also evolved
from these diagrams.

471
00:48:48.158 --> 00:48:49.819
I brought the markings.

472
00:48:50.961 --> 00:48:53.395
And if you put it on top the scripture...

473
00:48:54.898 --> 00:48:56.991
...they encircle Chinese characters.

474
00:48:58.168 --> 00:49:01.433
This one. <i>Fu.</i>
would mean "Liao Zheng Fu."

475
00:49:01.872 --> 00:49:05.137
And <i>Miao</i> would mean "Chiu Miao-fang."

476
00:49:05.575 --> 00:49:07.600
They happen to be the first two victims.

477
00:49:08.645 --> 00:49:10.442
And this one. <i>Jing...</i>

478
00:49:11.214 --> 00:49:12.806
...that one's more abstract.

479
00:49:13.750 --> 00:49:16.184
Perhaps it has something to do
with the fact that...

480
00:49:16.386 --> 00:49:18.820
...Lorenzo was a Christian pastor.

481
00:49:19.389 --> 00:49:22.825
When Christianity was
first introduced to China...

482
00:49:23.794 --> 00:49:27.355
...it was referred to as
the Jing religion.

483
00:49:28.732 --> 00:49:31.223
So our guy's using this pattern...

484
00:49:32.602 --> 00:49:34.263
...to search out the victims?

485
00:49:34.805 --> 00:49:38.206
All we can say. he's fulfilling
a thousand-year-old prophecy.

486
00:49:43.747 --> 00:49:45.544
You see this one?

487
00:49:47.017 --> 00:49:51.477
"The ones who don't believe in God."

488
00:49:52.089 --> 00:49:54.319
Which means "the nonbeliever."

489
00:49:58.428 --> 00:49:59.793
And this one is...

490
00:50:00.030 --> 00:50:05.832
..."yin and yang."

491
00:50:07.137 --> 00:50:09.435
All these are from the same diagram.

492
00:50:11.041 --> 00:50:14.499
Next victim could be a Wong.

493
00:50:17.414 --> 00:50:19.473
If according to this.

494
00:50:24.588 --> 00:50:26.180
Phil? Can we get on with it?

495
00:50:28.225 --> 00:50:31.251
<i>We're still not sure how to interpret</i>
<i>the evidence you sent us.</i>

496
00:50:32.229 --> 00:50:33.696
<i>However. we're sure of one thing.</i>

497
00:50:34.164 --> 00:50:37.258
<i>The mold in the victims' brains</i>
<i>isn't mold after all.</i>

498
00:50:37.434 --> 00:50:40.835
<i>It's a hybrid life form.</i>

499
00:50:41.505 --> 00:50:42.995
<i>A bug-born fungus.</i>

500
00:50:44.408 --> 00:50:47.309
<i>It's a variety</i>
<i>we haven't seen before.</i>

501
00:50:47.811 --> 00:50:52.077
<i>This is a kind of mite.</i>
<i>And these spores attach themselves.</i>

502
00:50:52.482 --> 00:50:55.974
So you're saying mites
carry the fungus to the brain?

503
00:50:56.219 --> 00:50:59.916
<i>Exactly. These insects seek out</i>
<i>the body warmth of living organisms.</i>

504
00:51:00.090 --> 00:51:02.388
<i>They'll find a host...</i>

505
00:51:02.592 --> 00:51:05.186
<i>... especially in small.</i>
<i>contained spaces.</i>

506
00:51:05.395 --> 00:51:10.094
<i>That's why the killer shot the fungus</i>
<i>into the a/c units. Very smart.</i>

507
00:51:10.467 --> 00:51:11.934
<i>The mites enter through the nose...</i>

508
00:51:12.102 --> 00:51:15.594
<i>... find their way up to the warm</i>
<i>brain and embed themselves.</i>

509
00:51:16.206 --> 00:51:18.640
<i>The victim doesn't feel a thing.</i>

510
00:51:18.942 --> 00:51:22.070
But were you able
to establish cause of death?

511
00:51:24.047 --> 00:51:25.241
<i>Yes and no.</i>

512
00:51:25.415 --> 00:51:27.645
<i>We found high amounts of serotonin...</i>

513
00:51:27.818 --> 00:51:30.013
<i>... and dopamine in the victims' blood.</i>

514
00:51:30.187 --> 00:51:31.484
What's dopamine?

515
00:51:32.589 --> 00:51:34.955
A naturally occurring chemical.

516
00:51:35.225 --> 00:51:36.214
Same as morphine.

517
00:51:36.393 --> 00:51:37.553
How much is "high"?

518
00:51:37.761 --> 00:51:39.991
- Are those elements toxic?
- <i>Not usually.</i>

519
00:51:40.230 --> 00:51:41.891
<i>Just the opposite. in fact.</i>

520
00:51:42.099 --> 00:51:44.260
<i>It's considered to be healing.</i>

521
00:51:44.501 --> 00:51:47.732
<i>The amount in the victims' blood</i>
<i>is about 50.000 times...</i>

522
00:51:48.004 --> 00:51:50.302
<i>... any previously recorded count.</i>

523
00:51:50.574 --> 00:51:54.374
<i>To secrete this amount. you'd</i>
<i>have to do a ton of cocaine...</i>

524
00:51:54.644 --> 00:51:57.704
<i>... and then have an orgasm</i>
<i>that lasts 40 years.</i>

525
00:51:58.181 --> 00:51:59.648
What a way to go.

526
00:52:01.284 --> 00:52:05.152
So you're saying the dopamine...

527
00:52:05.355 --> 00:52:08.483
...made the victims feel
like they were drowning...

528
00:52:08.658 --> 00:52:10.683
...or being consumed by fire?

529
00:52:11.161 --> 00:52:14.756
<i>Well. it could. Just like what</i>
<i>drugs do to the brain.</i>

530
00:52:16.066 --> 00:52:18.796
- Why different hallucinations?
- Yeah. why?

531
00:52:19.603 --> 00:52:22.697
Do you mean the killer
can control their delusions?

532
00:52:27.477 --> 00:52:29.468
<i>Actually. we don't know.</i>

533
00:52:29.713 --> 00:52:32.079
<i>None of this has ever been studied.</i>

534
00:52:47.864 --> 00:52:49.661
Only $ 100?

535
00:52:49.833 --> 00:52:52.529
- You can't give me two extra?
- The boss says no.

536
00:52:55.572 --> 00:53:00.066
- When do you get off tonight?
- I'll tell if you buy more.

537
00:53:00.277 --> 00:53:03.041
- Then give me a Mild Seven.
- Okay. Wait here.

538
00:53:08.418 --> 00:53:10.545
Do you need anything else?

539
00:53:14.124 --> 00:53:17.184
- What is your name?
- I'm Xiao Ya.

540
00:53:20.363 --> 00:53:23.799
- Shit. what are you honking about?
- I'll pick you up later.

541
00:53:31.474 --> 00:53:32.566
Huo-tu!

542
00:53:41.017 --> 00:53:42.109
Where to?

543
00:53:42.752 --> 00:53:43.946
Scene of a murder.

544
00:53:45.021 --> 00:53:46.613
This is from two days ago.

545
00:53:46.790 --> 00:53:48.257
The victim is Chen Liang-wang.

546
00:53:48.758 --> 00:53:51.386
His parents committed suicide.

547
00:53:51.861 --> 00:53:53.692
We called his home to check it out.

548
00:53:53.930 --> 00:53:57.195
They said he went to a s�ance
at a Taoist temple.

549
00:53:57.400 --> 00:54:00.301
He felt his parents had hid
his inheritance from him.

550
00:54:00.537 --> 00:54:02.630
Do we know which temple?

551
00:54:03.740 --> 00:54:05.037
I called to ask.

552
00:54:05.275 --> 00:54:08.403
There are at least 1000
temples around here.

553
00:54:17.187 --> 00:54:20.384
Li. long time no see!
What are you doing here?

554
00:54:20.657 --> 00:54:22.682
- We're here to visit you!
- Stop it!

555
00:54:22.892 --> 00:54:26.191
You are in the media everywhere.

556
00:54:26.429 --> 00:54:28.590
It's a pain in the ass.

557
00:54:28.765 --> 00:54:32.394
They're injured.
Gangsters of this neighborhood.

558
00:54:32.936 --> 00:54:36.838
- Is there a Chen Liang-wang?
- He's over there.

559
00:54:37.007 --> 00:54:38.099
What's the situation?

560
00:54:38.341 --> 00:54:43.108
A girl saw two bald guys
get into an argument over traffic.

561
00:54:43.346 --> 00:54:46.042
People came to watch.
and the van couldn't move.

562
00:54:46.249 --> 00:54:48.717
No one saw what actually happened.

563
00:54:48.952 --> 00:54:50.544
The bald guys killed the gangster?

564
00:54:54.357 --> 00:54:56.621
Looks like we got our fourth victim.

565
00:55:00.030 --> 00:55:04.364
He took a gun and suddenly
there was a loud scream.

566
00:55:04.601 --> 00:55:08.469
I couldn't see what they were doing.

567
00:55:08.738 --> 00:55:11.866
And things got confusing.

568
00:55:12.075 --> 00:55:16.910
A lot of people came over to watch...

569
00:55:17.147 --> 00:55:18.239
Richter.

570
00:55:35.632 --> 00:55:37.691
You okay with your noodles?

571
00:55:38.902 --> 00:55:43.896
- I hope they're not too hot for you.
- No. they're spicy.

572
00:55:45.475 --> 00:55:47.636
I'm from Texas. I like spicy food.

573
00:55:47.844 --> 00:55:52.076
Oh. yes? Then add more of this.
You'll like it.

574
00:55:55.685 --> 00:55:56.913
Thank you.

575
00:56:00.023 --> 00:56:01.547
I've been wondering.

576
00:56:02.792 --> 00:56:05.090
That bag of yours in the car...

577
00:56:06.863 --> 00:56:08.524
Are you religious?

578
00:56:09.599 --> 00:56:11.624
It's not relevant what I am.

579
00:56:19.242 --> 00:56:20.641
We are convinced...

580
00:56:20.877 --> 00:56:23.038
...that something impure could...

581
00:56:23.246 --> 00:56:25.578
...be lurking anywhere.
- Impure?

582
00:56:26.583 --> 00:56:29.017
Evil spirits. ghosts.

583
00:56:30.186 --> 00:56:33.678
The altar or the red bag is
for peace and prosperity.

584
00:56:33.890 --> 00:56:36.552
Most people believe in them.

585
00:56:37.660 --> 00:56:39.389
You haven't answered yet.

586
00:56:39.596 --> 00:56:41.086
Do you believe in them?

587
00:56:43.166 --> 00:56:45.031
We just don't understand...

588
00:56:45.235 --> 00:56:48.227
...why you can't see evil.
- We see it.

589
00:56:49.939 --> 00:56:53.067
- We lock it up sometimes.
- That's impossible.

590
00:56:53.243 --> 00:56:56.371
Look. I rely on science.

591
00:56:57.046 --> 00:56:59.879
Not talismans. not good-luck charms.

592
00:57:01.618 --> 00:57:04.086
Your so-called scientific methods...

593
00:57:04.287 --> 00:57:08.223
...are only useful when dealing
with mortals like ourselves.

594
00:57:08.625 --> 00:57:11.560
There are beings that cannot be
controlled by our laws.

595
00:57:11.761 --> 00:57:13.160
What are you saying?

596
00:57:15.465 --> 00:57:19.196
Are you saying that the killer
is an evil spirit...

597
00:57:21.471 --> 00:57:23.166
...or some kind of...

598
00:57:24.474 --> 00:57:26.203
...something from another world?

599
00:57:26.543 --> 00:57:28.602
What's wrong with you. Mr. Richter?

600
00:57:29.913 --> 00:57:32.143
In all your years with the FBI...

601
00:57:32.615 --> 00:57:35.311
...you have never encountered a demon?

602
00:57:42.826 --> 00:57:44.589
Now I see why you have a hard time...

603
00:57:44.761 --> 00:57:47.252
...fitting in with
your fellow officers.

604
00:57:51.267 --> 00:57:53.098
You're going to profile me?

605
00:57:54.804 --> 00:57:56.237
I am a suspect now?

606
00:58:13.356 --> 00:58:18.623
I may be a foreigner. but there
are some things that are universal.

607
00:58:20.096 --> 00:58:25.124
What you are doing to your family.
and yourself. I've seen it before.

608
00:58:27.470 --> 00:58:30.769
You gave me some advice before.
I'll return the favor.

609
00:58:30.974 --> 00:58:32.601
You're a brave man.

610
00:58:34.210 --> 00:58:36.576
You could be a great police officer.

611
00:58:38.481 --> 00:58:41.609
You exposed major corruption.
That took courage.

612
00:58:42.418 --> 00:58:44.318
- Courage?
- That's right. Courage.

613
00:58:44.587 --> 00:58:46.578
And that's in any language.

614
00:58:48.725 --> 00:58:52.661
Now you're just torturing yourself.

615
00:58:53.429 --> 00:58:56.057
Not many men
could've done what you did.

616
00:58:56.266 --> 00:58:58.962
You let your colleagues
treat you like a joke.

617
00:58:59.168 --> 00:59:00.567
You welcome it.

618
00:59:01.170 --> 00:59:04.731
You hide out in that office
and let your marriage go to shit.

619
00:59:07.176 --> 00:59:10.577
I've never fired a shot
since I joined the force.

620
00:59:11.414 --> 00:59:13.439
And I've never been under fire.

621
00:59:14.284 --> 00:59:15.911
But my daughter did...

622
00:59:16.553 --> 00:59:18.418
...by my own wife's cousin.

623
00:59:19.756 --> 00:59:23.248
And I just did nothing.
I did nothing to stop it.

624
00:59:23.459 --> 00:59:26.394
- Daddy!
- Don't come over!

625
00:59:26.930 --> 00:59:29.956
Put the gun down.
Put the gun down!

626
00:59:30.333 --> 00:59:31.857
- Yuan!
- Put your gun down.

627
00:59:33.503 --> 00:59:34.492
Put it down!

628
00:59:34.671 --> 00:59:37.162
- I've been sentenced to 15 years!
- Daddy.

629
00:59:37.440 --> 00:59:38.634
Mei-mei!

630
00:59:38.875 --> 00:59:41.469
I gave my life to the police force
for 15 years in jail?

631
00:59:41.678 --> 00:59:44.010
Yuan. don't do that.

632
00:59:44.247 --> 00:59:45.680
She is your own niece!

633
00:59:45.882 --> 00:59:48.407
We can appeal!

634
00:59:50.587 --> 00:59:52.350
We can still appeal!

635
00:59:52.589 --> 00:59:55.558
It's useless.
So what if I took the money?

636
00:59:55.725 --> 00:59:57.522
Think clearly about it.

637
00:59:57.760 --> 01:00:01.218
Huo-tu. Are you really so clean?

638
01:00:01.397 --> 01:00:04.560
You can't bear to see
someone have a better life?

639
01:00:06.836 --> 01:00:08.895
Your daddy forced me to do this.

640
01:00:15.979 --> 01:00:17.970
No!

641
01:00:25.655 --> 01:00:28.783
<i>His aim was off.</i>
<i>The bullet grazed her.</i>

642
01:00:29.559 --> 01:00:33.222
The doctor said she was unharmed
and would be fine.

643
01:00:34.430 --> 01:00:35.727
But he was wrong.

644
01:00:37.200 --> 01:00:40.465
Like you. he thought only of science.

645
01:00:47.110 --> 01:00:49.044
You asked what I believe in.

646
01:00:50.813 --> 01:00:53.805
I believe that she saw
something evil that day.

647
01:00:54.283 --> 01:00:55.910
And ever since...

648
01:00:56.619 --> 01:00:58.883
...she's been unable to speak again.

649
01:01:30.887 --> 01:01:31.945
<i>Who is it?</i>

650
01:01:32.121 --> 01:01:34.783
My name is Huang.
I'm looking for Dr. Sheng.

651
01:01:35.024 --> 01:01:38.152
<i>Do you know what time it is?</i>
<i>Dr. Sheng has gone to bed.</i>

652
01:01:38.327 --> 01:01:42.627
I'm sorry. I am a police officer.
This is urgent.

653
01:01:52.108 --> 01:01:56.602
This guy wants to attain immortality.
Why didn't you show me this before?

654
01:01:57.280 --> 01:01:58.372
Attain immortality?

655
01:01:58.581 --> 01:02:03.041
One branch of Taoism theorized
there are five kinds of hell.

656
01:02:03.619 --> 01:02:06.179
There is frigid hell...

657
01:02:06.689 --> 01:02:10.352
...fire hell. disembowelment hell.
heart-extraction hell...

658
01:02:10.560 --> 01:02:12.425
...and tongue-removal hell.

659
01:02:12.628 --> 01:02:16.359
After passing through
these five hells...

660
01:02:16.566 --> 01:02:20.127
...you attain immortality
in the sixth level.

661
01:02:20.403 --> 01:02:23.372
How to pass through the five tortures...

662
01:02:23.573 --> 01:02:27.100
...is something people cannot imagine.

663
01:02:27.376 --> 01:02:31.608
So the murderer killed
in order to attain...

664
01:02:32.048 --> 01:02:33.140
...immortality?

665
01:02:33.382 --> 01:02:35.247
According to history...

666
01:02:35.451 --> 01:02:38.386
...there was a Wong Shang
during the Sung Dynasty...

667
01:02:38.588 --> 01:02:43.048
...who is worshiped in Hong Kong's
Wong Tai Sin Temple.

668
01:02:43.693 --> 01:02:48.323
Before he attained immortality.
he killed many half-humans.

669
01:02:48.531 --> 01:02:51.989
These half-humans are
people who had committed sins...

670
01:02:52.235 --> 01:02:54.260
...and are neither human nor ghost.

671
01:02:54.504 --> 01:02:59.942
He must have used that theory to send
those man-ghosts to hell...

672
01:03:00.176 --> 01:03:02.007
...so he could attain sainthood.

673
01:03:02.779 --> 01:03:05.839
These four victims...

674
01:03:06.015 --> 01:03:09.075
...are presumably all morally corrupt.

675
01:03:09.252 --> 01:03:11.186
It's said that Wong Shang...

676
01:03:11.354 --> 01:03:14.846
...could write talismans
and perform rituals.

677
01:03:15.091 --> 01:03:17.559
He had double pupils.
which enabled him...

678
01:03:17.760 --> 01:03:22.254
...to see a thousand miles by day
and look at spirits by night.

679
01:03:22.565 --> 01:03:24.556
- Double pupils?
- Yes.

680
01:03:25.034 --> 01:03:28.526
Double pupils means...

681
01:03:28.738 --> 01:03:32.435
...that this person has two pupils...

682
01:03:34.143 --> 01:03:35.974
...in one eye.

683
01:03:37.046 --> 01:03:41.176
Only with two pupils
can one locate half-humans.

684
01:03:42.051 --> 01:03:44.315
From looking at his methods...

685
01:03:45.188 --> 01:03:47.679
...your murderer is quite something.

686
01:03:47.890 --> 01:03:52.691
He must have been gravely ill to be
able to distill this kind of potion.

687
01:03:54.597 --> 01:03:58.499
- Why must he be gravely ill?
- According to Taoism...

688
01:03:58.668 --> 01:04:01.364
...grave illness is essential
for attaining immortality.

689
01:04:01.571 --> 01:04:05.564
Only in grave illness can a person
experience real awakening.

690
01:04:07.009 --> 01:04:09.534
Dr. Shang. I found some words.

691
01:04:09.812 --> 01:04:12.838
Yin and yang.
Do you know what that means?

692
01:04:13.416 --> 01:04:15.475
According to the lunar diagram...

693
01:04:16.853 --> 01:04:22.758
...these "Chi" represent
from May to July...

694
01:04:23.259 --> 01:04:26.490
...they also represent
fire. <i>Huo.</i> and earth. <i>Tu.</i>

695
01:04:35.771 --> 01:04:39.104
Excuse me.
Hello?

696
01:04:40.710 --> 01:04:44.646
- Where are you?
- Surfing the Web with some teenagers.

697
01:04:44.814 --> 01:04:47.578
That Styrofoam we found
inside the killer's van?

698
01:04:48.818 --> 01:04:51.480
It's a type of Styrofoam used
to prevent static electricity.

699
01:04:52.588 --> 01:04:54.852
The windows were covered
with a special material.

700
01:04:55.491 --> 01:04:58.483
A heat-isolating layer
shuts out ultraviolet rays.

701
01:04:58.995 --> 01:05:00.690
Now. in the U. S...

702
01:05:01.330 --> 01:05:05.266
...both are used in delivery vans
for integrated-circuit units.

703
01:05:07.036 --> 01:05:10.972
All our evidence points to suspects
with a high-tech industry background.

704
01:05:12.074 --> 01:05:16.306
We're not looking for delivery men.
These guys are highly placed.

705
01:05:22.785 --> 01:05:24.082
Dr. Sheng.

706
01:05:26.222 --> 01:05:27.655
Excuse me for asking.

707
01:05:27.890 --> 01:05:30.450
Do you believe in this
"attaining immortality"?

708
01:05:31.227 --> 01:05:33.957
If I told you yes.
you would immediately...

709
01:05:34.163 --> 01:05:35.721
...doubt my authority.

710
01:05:38.167 --> 01:05:39.429
Officer Huang...

711
01:05:39.769 --> 01:05:41.760
...if you ask me...

712
01:05:42.338 --> 01:05:45.739
...whether I believe in
Taoist immortals...

713
01:05:45.975 --> 01:05:48.239
...or in aliens...

714
01:05:48.911 --> 01:05:51.402
...I would not choose aliens.

715
01:06:01.057 --> 01:06:04.458
This delivery van
belongs to Cutting Edge.

716
01:06:04.694 --> 01:06:06.525
HSINCHU SCIENCE PARK
ADMINISTRATION

717
01:06:06.696 --> 01:06:10.792
- It no longer exists.
- What does that mean?

718
01:06:11.634 --> 01:06:14.569
Cutting Edge was
an IC design company...

719
01:06:14.770 --> 01:06:17.330
...owned by two guys who got
their Ph.D.'s from America.

720
01:06:17.907 --> 01:06:19.738
They made a lot of money.

721
01:06:19.942 --> 01:06:23.139
But they got caught up in religion.

722
01:06:23.346 --> 01:06:27.749
In the end. they sold the company
for $2 billion.

723
01:06:28.017 --> 01:06:32.613
- And the two went off to become monks.
- Do you have any data on them?

724
01:06:34.690 --> 01:06:38.285
It's printing. These people
are really fanatical.

725
01:06:38.461 --> 01:06:41.191
They spent a lot of money
to ship a temple...

726
01:06:41.430 --> 01:06:43.990
...from mainland China.
The whole thing.

727
01:06:44.266 --> 01:06:48.999
A historical relic. They took
the temple down. piece by piece...

728
01:06:49.205 --> 01:06:54.268
...then put it back together.
How crazy.

729
01:06:59.115 --> 01:07:00.446
Where is it?

730
01:07:34.683 --> 01:07:35.945
Open up.

731
01:07:36.752 --> 01:07:38.811
Open up! Police business!

732
01:07:45.594 --> 01:07:49.655
Christ! How'd they fit
this temple in there?

733
01:08:17.393 --> 01:08:21.090
Which one of you is Lin Tao-sheng?
And Huang Yi-feng?

734
01:08:25.167 --> 01:08:28.568
Lin Tao-sheng. Huang Yi-feng.

735
01:08:33.843 --> 01:08:35.834
You are the people in charge here?

736
01:08:36.078 --> 01:08:38.342
- We don't have anyone in charge.
- Bullshit!

737
01:08:38.581 --> 01:08:40.344
You didn't register for a license?

738
01:08:43.252 --> 01:08:44.810
What are these?

739
01:08:46.322 --> 01:08:47.311
Take them all away.

740
01:08:47.523 --> 01:08:48.615
- Bring them.
- Move it.

741
01:08:48.791 --> 01:08:51.351
- Be cooperative.
- You've violated arms-control laws.

742
01:08:51.594 --> 01:08:53.585
- Hurry!
- Move it!

743
01:08:53.796 --> 01:08:55.263
Take them away!

744
01:08:57.133 --> 01:08:58.862
What is this temple?

745
01:08:59.201 --> 01:09:01.692
- Did you register it?
- What is inside there?

746
01:09:02.004 --> 01:09:03.471
Out of the way.

747
01:09:26.362 --> 01:09:30.890
- <i>Officer down! Help!</i>
- Send backup now!

748
01:09:32.268 --> 01:09:33.257
Hurry up!

749
01:10:34.763 --> 01:10:36.094
Break the lock!

750
01:12:30.579 --> 01:12:33.514
This is Li Yun-chan at the scene
of the massacre...

751
01:12:33.682 --> 01:12:36.344
...that took place inside
the Central World Building.

752
01:12:36.552 --> 01:12:40.386
Nine officers and 24 members
of the True Sage cult...

753
01:12:40.656 --> 01:12:42.385
...are listed as dead.

754
01:12:42.658 --> 01:12:47.925
It has been confirmed that
Huang Yi-feng was killed.

755
01:12:50.999 --> 01:12:53.024
- Among them are professors. doctors...

756
01:12:53.235 --> 01:12:56.568
...police officers
and even politicians.

757
01:12:56.772 --> 01:12:59.707
Acting on new information.
police raided 50...

758
01:14:07.643 --> 01:14:10.806
Officer Huang. the foreigner
inside wants to see you.

759
01:14:25.194 --> 01:14:26.684
What's happened?

760
01:14:27.296 --> 01:14:28.786
I found something.

761
01:14:39.041 --> 01:14:40.372
Come help.

762
01:14:44.880 --> 01:14:45.904
Pull!

763
01:14:55.691 --> 01:14:57.352
What the hell?

764
01:15:28.023 --> 01:15:29.786
She needs an ambulance!

765
01:15:30.692 --> 01:15:31.852
Stretcher!

766
01:15:32.628 --> 01:15:34.357
Emergency! Hurry!

767
01:15:36.031 --> 01:15:38.295
Out of the way!

768
01:15:43.405 --> 01:15:46.135
Agent Richter! Agent Richter!

769
01:15:46.408 --> 01:15:49.935
Can you give your views
on these strange murders?

770
01:15:50.145 --> 01:15:53.774
My personal view's unimportant.
Get your cable off me!

771
01:15:56.552 --> 01:15:59.214
There's talk of supernatural
aspects to these crimes.

772
01:15:59.421 --> 01:16:01.821
That the killer wanted
to attain immortality.

773
01:16:02.024 --> 01:16:03.321
They definitely failed.

774
01:16:03.525 --> 01:16:07.518
But some officers have experienced
supernatural phenomena.

775
01:16:07.729 --> 01:16:09.697
Can you comment on that?

776
01:16:20.142 --> 01:16:22.133
Hey! How is...?

777
01:16:23.478 --> 01:16:25.446
Your captain. how is he?

778
01:16:26.648 --> 01:16:30.209
Got some 30 stitches.
You could even see his ribs.

779
01:16:30.452 --> 01:16:31.851
I'll go see him.

780
01:16:32.354 --> 01:16:36.051
He's under sedation.
The doctors want him to rest.

781
01:16:42.197 --> 01:16:43.687
And the girl?

782
01:16:45.000 --> 01:16:48.868
Her condition isn't critical.
She was already ill anyway.

783
01:16:49.605 --> 01:16:51.539
What do you mean she was ill?

784
01:16:54.309 --> 01:16:57.540
"Hsieh Ya-li.
Benign brain tumor exerts pressure...

785
01:16:57.746 --> 01:17:01.113
...on her pituitary gland
and optic chiasma and expands...

786
01:17:01.383 --> 01:17:05.479
...to both sides of the forehead.
Condition deemed inoperable."

787
01:17:05.921 --> 01:17:07.980
How about the injury
on her belly?

788
01:17:08.190 --> 01:17:12.422
The skin on her belly
had been peeled off...

789
01:17:12.661 --> 01:17:16.893
...and was used to cultivate...
What's it called? A bug-born fungus.

790
01:17:19.868 --> 01:17:23.269
The bureau has notified me
that Lin Tao-sheng...

791
01:17:23.438 --> 01:17:26.737
...has confessed to the murders.

792
01:17:30.278 --> 01:17:31.540
Case closed.

793
01:18:11.920 --> 01:18:14.320
Where do you want to eat?
It's my treat.

794
01:18:14.556 --> 01:18:19.823
No. it's mine. Those noodles of yours
almost killed me last time.

795
01:18:21.797 --> 01:18:24.322
Since it's my last night here...

796
01:18:24.833 --> 01:18:27.495
...I thought we'd do something more
appropriate.

797
01:18:28.804 --> 01:18:30.795
Got some directions here.

798
01:18:32.407 --> 01:18:35.672
Take a left at this next street.
Yeah.

799
01:18:39.481 --> 01:18:40.675
And...?

800
01:18:41.249 --> 01:18:42.876
And then. you...

801
01:18:45.654 --> 01:18:48.282
...take a right
at the next light. I think.

802
01:18:48.557 --> 01:18:50.548
- It's the one after.
- Oh.

803
01:18:51.426 --> 01:18:52.620
Okay.

804
01:18:54.896 --> 01:18:56.488
You take it from here.

805
01:19:03.138 --> 01:19:05.732
Hey. you are late.
Dinner is ready.

806
01:19:05.907 --> 01:19:08.205
- Good. I'm starving.
- Welcome. welcome.

807
01:19:08.443 --> 01:19:09.603
Thank you.

808
01:19:12.214 --> 01:19:14.239
Hi. Welcome home.

809
01:19:23.125 --> 01:19:27.755
So you're not interested in staying
more days as a tourist?

810
01:19:30.031 --> 01:19:32.556
You will remember us only for death.

811
01:19:33.401 --> 01:19:37.531
Actually. the true beauty
of the island is on the East Coast.

812
01:19:37.706 --> 01:19:40.197
Like Su-ao. a little fishing village.

813
01:19:40.509 --> 01:19:42.875
Huang was born there. Very pretty.

814
01:19:43.111 --> 01:19:45.170
Well. it sounds nice.

815
01:19:46.214 --> 01:19:50.617
But to be perfectly honest with you.
I'm a little homesick.

816
01:19:51.186 --> 01:19:54.121
Been a long time.
the job's done and...

817
01:19:56.191 --> 01:20:00.628
Well. you know what? I got a week's
vacation coming at Christmas...

818
01:20:00.829 --> 01:20:02.854
...and maybe you two
will have me back.

819
01:20:04.533 --> 01:20:06.763
- Show me around.
- Sure.

820
01:20:06.935 --> 01:20:08.630
If it's not too cold.

821
01:20:10.438 --> 01:20:12.906
Compared to the States.
we never get too cold.

822
01:20:13.275 --> 01:20:14.606
Then it's a date.

823
01:20:17.412 --> 01:20:19.141
Here's to Huo-tu's wife.

824
01:20:21.483 --> 01:20:22.916
And to Mei-mei.

825
01:20:25.754 --> 01:20:29.212
And this meal
and your gracious hospitality.

826
01:20:30.492 --> 01:20:32.323
And thank your mother.

827
01:20:34.663 --> 01:20:36.290
What's so funny?

828
01:20:36.765 --> 01:20:38.392
Someone tell me what's so funny.

829
01:20:38.600 --> 01:20:39.624
Mei-mei.

830
01:20:43.505 --> 01:20:46.941
- It's my fault.
- Somebody tell me what's so funny.

831
01:20:48.076 --> 01:20:49.839
It's my fault.

832
01:20:51.813 --> 01:20:53.178
Go to sleep.

833
01:21:01.489 --> 01:21:05.084
<i>It'd be a lot easier for us</i>
<i>if there were evil spirits.</i>

834
01:21:06.528 --> 01:21:10.294
<i>Unfortunately. man is worse than</i>
<i>any figment of our imagination.</i>

835
01:21:11.132 --> 01:21:14.624
- You're good.
- I am. aren't I?

836
01:21:15.537 --> 01:21:18.597
I give these things
dozens of times a year.

837
01:21:19.207 --> 01:21:22.108
Now I am just tired.

838
01:21:22.744 --> 01:21:26.703
I'm tired of... Tired of pretending.

839
01:21:28.984 --> 01:21:30.645
Everything is...

840
01:21:31.486 --> 01:21:34.887
Everything is under control.

841
01:21:36.658 --> 01:21:38.148
Until the next...

842
01:21:38.894 --> 01:21:41.294
...atrocity comes along.

843
01:21:43.265 --> 01:21:44.493
And it will.

844
01:21:47.435 --> 01:21:49.630
More and more. I just want to...

845
01:21:50.572 --> 01:21:54.975
I just want to scream. I don't want
to talk. just scream.

846
01:22:04.786 --> 01:22:08.119
You and your wife. why don't you
sleep in the same room?

847
01:22:09.758 --> 01:22:10.850
No.

848
01:22:11.626 --> 01:22:14.186
Mei-mei always gets nightmares.

849
01:22:15.430 --> 01:22:18.991
She feels more comfortable
when her mom's around.

850
01:22:19.200 --> 01:22:20.565
Don't you miss...?

851
01:22:23.605 --> 01:22:25.766
How long has it been since...?

852
01:22:28.910 --> 01:22:33.176
Is there any question too personal
for an American to ask?

853
01:22:33.381 --> 01:22:35.372
Yes. definitely.

854
01:22:36.751 --> 01:22:38.514
- But not me.
- So...

855
01:22:39.621 --> 01:22:43.079
So tell me about your family.
Your wife.

856
01:22:48.463 --> 01:22:50.397
My wife is long gone.

857
01:22:51.733 --> 01:22:54.566
How come you still
wear your wedding ring?

858
01:23:01.643 --> 01:23:03.133
Ready for another one?

859
01:23:04.112 --> 01:23:05.238
- I'll get it.
- I will.

860
01:23:05.413 --> 01:23:07.313
- No. no.
- I'll get it.

861
01:23:09.484 --> 01:23:10.781
Maybe not.

862
01:23:48.023 --> 01:23:49.047
What?

863
01:23:50.025 --> 01:23:51.322
What is it?

864
01:24:27.429 --> 01:24:28.418
Kevin.

865
01:24:29.898 --> 01:24:31.422
Time to get up.

866
01:24:34.436 --> 01:24:35.630
Kevin.

867
01:24:36.738 --> 01:24:38.638
You've got a flight to catch.

868
01:25:18.980 --> 01:25:20.845
What the hell is going on?

869
01:25:21.816 --> 01:25:23.306
Didn't you sleep here
last night?

870
01:25:24.018 --> 01:25:26.179
- Not ask so many questions.

871
01:25:27.288 --> 01:25:30.052
What the hell
are you mumbling about?

872
01:25:31.893 --> 01:25:35.158
Too much. So many questions.

873
01:25:41.369 --> 01:25:43.200
There's mold in his nasal cavity.

874
01:25:43.404 --> 01:25:45.531
Like the victims before him.

875
01:25:47.041 --> 01:25:51.535
It looks like he just
yanked off his own tongue.

876
01:25:54.649 --> 01:25:58.881
How is it possible
that he was harmed. but not you?

877
01:26:15.003 --> 01:26:16.766
Get the doctor. quick!

878
01:26:19.507 --> 01:26:21.805
- What are you saying?
- Mei-mei...

879
01:26:22.043 --> 01:26:23.635
...is talking to me.

880
01:26:24.746 --> 01:26:26.475
Out of the way.

881
01:26:27.448 --> 01:26:29.279
What poison has he taken?

882
01:26:30.351 --> 01:26:33.752
- I don't know.
- Why is there so much serotonin?

883
01:26:34.422 --> 01:26:35.912
Two cc's haloperidol.

884
01:26:36.524 --> 01:26:37.889
IV push.

885
01:26:38.626 --> 01:26:40.560
Tell me. how he is doing?

886
01:26:40.929 --> 01:26:42.829
- What happened?
- Family will wait outside!

887
01:26:43.064 --> 01:26:44.588
Please tell me how he is.

888
01:26:44.832 --> 01:26:47.130
He is probably flying through space.

889
01:26:49.671 --> 01:26:52.765
<i>In Taiwan. less than 24 hours</i>
<i>after being interviewed...</i>

890
01:26:52.941 --> 01:26:57.310
<i>... on the True Sage serial killings.</i>
<i>FBI Agent Kevin Richter...</i>

891
01:26:57.579 --> 01:27:00.480
<i>... has been found murdered</i>
<i>in a Taipei apartment.</i>

892
01:27:00.815 --> 01:27:05.309
<i>He is the latest victim in what was</i>
<i>thought to be a solved case.</i>

893
01:27:05.720 --> 01:27:09.918
<i>Another theory claims he was killed to</i>
<i>complete the fifth path to immortality.</i>

894
01:27:10.258 --> 01:27:13.955
<i>Richter publicly claimed he didn't</i>
<i>believe in spirits or demons.</i>

895
01:27:14.229 --> 01:27:17.960
<i>He was therefore condemned to</i>
<i>the tongue-extracting punishment...</i>

896
01:27:18.233 --> 01:27:19.530
<i>... for the unbeliever.</i>

897
01:27:19.734 --> 01:27:22.498
<i>To understand Richter's death.</i>
<i>one has to go...</i>

898
01:27:24.138 --> 01:27:25.935
- these "Chi" represent
from May to July...

899
01:27:26.107 --> 01:27:28.940
...they also represent
fire. <i>Huo.</i> and earth. <i>Tu.</i>

900
01:27:29.244 --> 01:27:31.576
<i>The murder is quite something.</i>

901
01:27:31.779 --> 01:27:36.113
<i>He must be gravely ill to be able</i>
<i>to distill a potion like this.</i>

902
01:27:36.417 --> 01:27:37.975
<i>Why must he be gravely ill?</i>

903
01:27:38.186 --> 01:27:39.813
<i>According to Taoism...</i>

904
01:27:40.355 --> 01:27:42.755
<i>... grave illness is essential</i>
<i>for attaining immortality.</i>

905
01:27:43.091 --> 01:27:47.027
<i>Only in grave illness can a person</i>
<i>experience real awakening.</i>

906
01:28:45.820 --> 01:28:49.153
Where's that girl? Hsieh Ya-li?

907
01:28:49.824 --> 01:28:51.792
I'm a police officer.

908
01:28:53.594 --> 01:28:56.154
- She's disappeared.
- Disappeared?

909
01:28:56.497 --> 01:29:00.593
Just disappeared.
Since this afternoon.

910
01:29:03.071 --> 01:29:05.505
Aren't you...? Aren't you the guy...?

911
01:29:05.807 --> 01:29:07.604
EMERGENC Y ROOM

912
01:29:10.144 --> 01:29:11.475
<i>Ching Fang.</i>

913
01:29:13.014 --> 01:29:15.380
- Central World Building.
- <i>Are you there?</i>

914
01:29:15.616 --> 01:29:17.311
<i>I don't know what happened.</i>

915
01:29:17.518 --> 01:29:19.281
<i>I am unable to wake up.</i>

916
01:29:19.887 --> 01:29:24.915
<i>The girl who is sick</i>
<i>is coming to see me.</i>

917
01:29:25.226 --> 01:29:28.320
<i>She told me that</i>
<i>she killed everyone.</i>

918
01:29:28.663 --> 01:29:32.929
<i>She hides in the cave</i>
<i>and meditates.</i>

919
01:29:33.568 --> 01:29:37.026
<i>She found me</i>
<i>according to the scriptures.</i>

920
01:29:38.506 --> 01:29:42.101
<i>She also said</i>
<i>all her disciples are gone now.</i>

921
01:29:43.378 --> 01:29:44.709
<i>But she is not afraid.</i>

922
01:29:44.912 --> 01:29:46.937
<i>She can still be immortal.</i>

923
01:29:47.915 --> 01:29:49.815
<i>It will not be an obstacle.</i>

924
01:29:55.456 --> 01:29:56.923
<i>Ching Fang.</i>

925
01:29:58.359 --> 01:29:59.621
<i>Are you there?</i>

926
01:30:01.095 --> 01:30:02.619
<i>Anyone there?</i>

927
01:30:03.898 --> 01:30:05.160
<i>Hello?</i>

928
01:32:17.999 --> 01:32:19.489
Who are you?

929
01:32:20.568 --> 01:32:22.559
What the hell do you want?

930
01:32:23.137 --> 01:32:26.129
Everything has already been destined.

931
01:32:27.108 --> 01:32:29.906
You came to see me off. Come.

932
01:32:31.145 --> 01:32:35.605
To hell with you! I am a police officer.
You are under arrest.

933
01:32:35.850 --> 01:32:39.149
On your knees.
Hands behind your back.

934
01:32:40.154 --> 01:32:44.113
You seem so sad.
Do you need me to help you?

935
01:32:48.763 --> 01:32:52.927
Come. Come back to
the hospital with me.

936
01:32:54.969 --> 01:32:58.871
Really?
Can the hospital help you?

937
01:33:02.877 --> 01:33:05.072
Would you rather have Mei-mei here?

938
01:33:08.449 --> 01:33:11.907
Maybe she can help you.

939
01:33:16.223 --> 01:33:17.588
Daddy!

940
01:33:18.192 --> 01:33:20.626
Yuan! Don't shoot! Yuan!

941
01:33:20.795 --> 01:33:23.161
Your daddy forced me to do this.

942
01:33:24.098 --> 01:33:25.963
- Yuan!
- Daddy!

943
01:33:31.772 --> 01:33:33.000
Huo-tu!

944
01:33:33.674 --> 01:33:38.008
Have you ever really cared about us?
Have you really needed us?

945
01:34:07.541 --> 01:34:10.305
Come on. Shoot me too.

946
01:34:13.748 --> 01:34:15.045
Help me.

947
01:34:16.651 --> 01:34:21.987
I don't believe people
can attain immortality.

948
01:34:24.191 --> 01:34:27.820
I am a police officer.
Foreign Affairs division.

949
01:34:28.929 --> 01:34:32.558
I am arresting you as a suspect...

950
01:34:33.701 --> 01:34:35.396
...of serial murders.

951
01:34:49.617 --> 01:34:51.847
This is not real.

952
01:34:57.258 --> 01:34:58.725
I am...

953
01:34:59.527 --> 01:35:02.018
...Huang Huo-tu.

954
01:35:03.531 --> 01:35:07.092
I neglected the lives
of my wife and daughter.

955
01:35:07.735 --> 01:35:10.727
And ignored the deaths
of my colleagues.

956
01:35:11.105 --> 01:35:14.871
You think I will help you?
Come on.

957
01:35:15.076 --> 01:35:16.304
Come on!

958
01:35:18.112 --> 01:35:19.306
Give it to me!

959
01:35:19.547 --> 01:35:23.813
One shot and your heart
will stop instantly.

960
01:35:24.185 --> 01:35:27.416
Your body will respond as if
you died from a gunshot.

961
01:35:28.522 --> 01:35:32.049
You know when you die.
your wife and Mei-mei...

962
01:35:32.259 --> 01:35:34.352
What will their lives be like?

963
01:35:38.399 --> 01:35:40.196
So pathetic!

964
01:35:40.401 --> 01:35:42.665
With no one to take care of them.

965
01:36:02.890 --> 01:36:05.518
EMERGENCY ROOM

966
01:36:13.100 --> 01:36:14.124
Huo-tu.

967
01:36:14.602 --> 01:36:16.069
Are you all right?

968
01:36:17.671 --> 01:36:19.468
Where's the girl?

969
01:36:19.673 --> 01:36:21.072
Inside.

970
01:36:21.475 --> 01:36:22.942
Is she badly injured?

971
01:36:24.512 --> 01:36:27.345
The bullet didn't enter.
It grazed her skull.

972
01:36:28.783 --> 01:36:32.947
Did you check her eyes?
Is there anything unusual about them?

973
01:36:33.154 --> 01:36:34.451
Unusual?

974
01:36:34.655 --> 01:36:37.317
Does she have two pupils in one eye?

975
01:36:39.927 --> 01:36:41.155
Come with me.

976
01:36:43.364 --> 01:36:46.458
Seventeen years ago.
her mother gave birth here.

977
01:36:46.667 --> 01:36:50.831
She gave birth to twins.
One was stillborn. She was the other.

978
01:36:51.038 --> 01:36:54.599
She was never a happy child.
No one to care for her.

979
01:36:54.775 --> 01:36:58.939
They found a tumor in her brain.
She claimed she could see things.

980
01:36:59.146 --> 01:37:02.479
You know what I mean?
She said she could see her sister.

981
01:37:03.217 --> 01:37:08.814
This is not unusual.
Brain-tumor patients react like this.

982
01:37:09.056 --> 01:37:13.117
It's like they're on drugs.
Like they're possessed.

983
01:37:13.928 --> 01:37:16.726
It's difficult
to explain scientifically.

984
01:37:16.931 --> 01:37:22.335
During her stay here. she found out
about her stillborn twin and changed.

985
01:37:22.570 --> 01:37:25.061
She said her sister was not dead...

986
01:37:25.773 --> 01:37:30.233
...but had attained immortality.
The double pupils prove this.

987
01:37:47.628 --> 01:37:49.186
You scared me.

988
01:37:50.130 --> 01:37:53.031
- Are you all right?
- I am now.

989
01:37:54.368 --> 01:37:55.494
Where's Mei-mei?

990
01:37:56.770 --> 01:38:00.365
Sleeping.
I'll wake her up for dinner.

991
01:38:01.976 --> 01:38:04.467
Sleeping? Is she ill?

992
01:38:18.058 --> 01:38:20.151
DIVORCE AGREEMENT

993
01:38:24.398 --> 01:38:26.457
SIGNED AND EXECUTED

994
01:38:39.980 --> 01:38:45.247
Get up! Think you can
get away with this?

995
01:38:45.819 --> 01:38:48.310
Can you hear me? Get up!

996
01:38:48.522 --> 01:38:51.980
- Ching Fang.
- Like father. like daughter!

997
01:38:52.226 --> 01:38:54.717
I'm telling you to get up!

998
01:38:58.065 --> 01:38:59.225
Huo-tu.

999
01:39:00.534 --> 01:39:03.059
I don't know what to do with her.

1000
01:39:04.104 --> 01:39:06.595
Say you're sorry.
Apologize.

1001
01:39:06.840 --> 01:39:08.603
What are you doing?

1002
01:40:04.098 --> 01:40:05.861
I must go.

1003
01:40:07.701 --> 01:40:10.101
You will come with me too.

1004
01:40:26.120 --> 01:40:28.281
It has all been ordained.

1005
01:40:35.662 --> 01:40:37.323
Don't be afraid.

1006
01:40:37.965 --> 01:40:39.364
I'm not afraid.

1007
01:40:41.969 --> 01:40:43.493
Be brave.

1008
01:40:49.643 --> 01:40:51.770
I'm going now.

1009
01:41:33.454 --> 01:41:34.580
Huo-tu!

1010
01:41:36.924 --> 01:41:38.118
<i>Huo-tu!</i>

1011
01:41:39.226 --> 01:41:43.060
I want to review the reports
before they go to your superiors.

1012
01:41:44.364 --> 01:41:47.856
Where's Huo-tu?
Where's Huo-tu?

1013
01:41:50.137 --> 01:41:51.866
That's not him!

1014
01:41:52.072 --> 01:41:54.540
That's the girl.

1015
01:42:08.489 --> 01:42:10.389
He did not suffer.

1016
01:42:19.333 --> 01:42:22.461
We gave him CPR for a long time.
We did our best.

1017
01:42:38.952 --> 01:42:40.078
Wake up.

1018
01:42:43.123 --> 01:42:44.283
Wake up.

1019
01:42:45.559 --> 01:42:48.619
I know you can hear me.

1020
01:42:49.530 --> 01:42:51.361
Wake up. Can you hear me?

1021
01:42:51.832 --> 01:42:53.732
He inhaled too much mold bacteria.

1022
01:42:54.735 --> 01:42:56.430
His heart couldn't take it.

1023
01:42:58.539 --> 01:43:00.939
Wake up. Wake up!

1024
01:43:01.909 --> 01:43:04.400
- Let him go!
- No. I have to try!

1025
01:43:04.978 --> 01:43:07.105
I know he can hear me!

1026
01:43:07.848 --> 01:43:11.443
I will get him back.
I will get him back!

1027
01:43:11.752 --> 01:43:14.084
Come back!

1028
01:43:16.023 --> 01:43:19.959
You can't abandon me and Mei-mei!

1029
01:43:20.160 --> 01:43:22.685
Come back!

1030
01:43:24.831 --> 01:43:26.298
Come back.

1031
01:43:40.047 --> 01:43:43.539
Tell your father to wake up.

1032
01:43:52.793 --> 01:43:55.819
Mommy. Mommy?

1033
01:43:56.597 --> 01:43:58.963
What is Daddy laughing at?

1034
01:44:00.133 --> 01:44:01.464
Daddy loves you...

1035
01:44:01.668 --> 01:44:05.160
...but doesn't know how to tell you.
so all he can do is smile.

1036
01:44:12.579 --> 01:44:14.137
Daddy.

1037
01:44:18.986 --> 01:44:20.453
Daddy.

1038
01:44:35.636 --> 01:44:38.469
Look at his eyes.

1039
01:44:44.478 --> 01:44:45.570
Paramedics!

1040
01:44:47.014 --> 01:44:49.744
Get him to the hospital!

1041
01:44:50.250 --> 01:44:51.774
He's crying!

1042
01:45:43.303 --> 01:45:45.498
If you have loved. you will never die.

1043
01:45:46.305 --> 01:46:46.187
